Here are four whiskey-based cocktails featuring various fruits and fruit-flavored ingredients:

**1. Strawberry Whiskey Smash**

*Ingredients:*
- Fresh strawberries
- Fresh basil leaves
- 2 oz whiskey
- 1 oz lemon juice
- ½ oz simple syrup
- Club soda (optional)
- Ice
- Strawberry or basil sprig for garnish

*Recipe:* Muddle fresh strawberries and basil leaves in a shaker. Add whiskey, lemon juice, and simple syrup. Fill with ice and shake well. Strain into an ice-filled glass. Top with club soda if desired. Garnish with a strawberry slice or basil sprig.

*Source:* [DineWithDrinks](https://dinewithdrinks.com/best-fruity-whiskey-cocktails)

**2. Blackberry Bourbon Lemonade**

*Ingredients:*
- Fresh blackberries
- 2 oz bourbon
- 1 oz lemon juice
- ½ oz simple syrup
- Sparkling wine
- Ice
- Lemon wheel and blackberries for garnish

*Recipe:* Muddle blackberries in a shaker. Add bourbon, lemon juice, and simple syrup. Fill with ice and shake well. Strain into an ice-filled glass. Top with sparkling wine. Garnish with a lemon wheel and blackberries.

*Source:* [Whisky Advocate](https://whiskyadvocate.com/fruity-whiskey-cocktails/)

**3. Peach Whiskey Iced Tea**

*Ingredients:*
- Fresh peach slices
- 2 oz whiskey
- 1 oz lemon juice
- Sweetened iced tea
- Ice
- Peach slice or mint sprig for garnish

*Recipe:* Muddle peach slices in a shaker. Add whiskey and lemon juice. Fill with ice and shake well. Strain into an ice-filled glass. Top with sweetened iced tea. Garnish with a peach slice or mint sprig.

*Source:* [Drink Celebration](https://drinkcelebration.com/whiskey/best-fruit-whiskey-cocktails/)

**4. Passion Fruit Bourbon Sour**

*Ingredients:*
- 2 oz bourbon
- 1 oz passion fruit syrup
- ¾ oz lime juice
- 1 egg white (optional)
- Angostura bitters
- Ice
- Lime wheel for garnish

*Recipe:* Combine bourbon, passion fruit syrup, lime juice, and egg white in a shaker. Dry shake (without ice) to emulsify. Add ice and shake again. Strain into a chilled glass. Top with a few dashes of Angostura bitters. Garnish with a lime wheel.

*Source:* [Insanely Good Recipes](https://insanelygoodrecipes.com/whiskey-cocktails/)

